cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about machine translation using deep neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic models and hyperparameters, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The exploration is performed on a specific task, German-English translation, which involves processing and analyzing visual data, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the training process and optimization techniques, which are common topics in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
